criteria.textblock:
Inclusion Criteria:
- Clinical suspicion of low back pain of facet origin
- Are over 18 years old
- Have the ability to understand the study protocol, to voluntarily complete or through their companions the free and informed consent and to answer the questionnaires before infiltration and by telephone contact in the follow-up.
Exclusion Criteria:
- Congenital or acquired deformities of the lumbar spine;
- Fracture or sequel of lumbar spine fracture of traumatic, pathological or osteoporotic origin
- Surgical manipulation of the lumbar spine;
- Age under 18 years;
- MRI scans of limited quality and incomplete sequences,
- Diabetes;
- Use of systemic corticosteroids less than 1 month before the procedure;
- Facet infiltration with corticoid in the last year;
- Phone contact failures during follow-up.
- Antecedents of allergy to anesthetic.
- Pregnant or breastfeeding.
- Lumbar spine stenosis.
- Symptomatic radiculopathy.
- History of adverse reaction to corticosteroids.
